FBIS4-12195 "drnes066dd_94001" FBIS-NES-94-066 Daily Report 3 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs Fatah Warns Against `Negative Phenomena' in Society Fatah Warns Against `Negative Phenomena' in Society TA0504155294 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 3 Apr 94 p 2 TA0504155294 Jerusalem AL-QUDS Arabic BFN [By special AL-QUDS correspondent] [Text] Rafah -- Fatah issued a statement in which it warned Palestinians against some of the negative phenomena that have begun to be entrenched in society. It called for unifying efforts, potentials, and capabilities for the coming stage. In its statement, Fatah referred to the phenomenon of the use and spread of weapons. It said: We do not want a militia state. The future belongs to knowledge and renovation. It accused the Israeli Government of being behind the spread of this phenomenon. The statement also referred to the phenomenon of infringing upon public property and building on it for private purposes. The statement mentioned the phenomenon of stopping traffic, and called on drivers to keep order by themselves. The statement called on all Palestinian factions to unify efforts and adopt a collective stance toward these negative phenomena.
